The paper deals with simultaneous embeddings of directed graphs, which is a topic in graph theory and computational geometry. Specifically, it focuses on monotone simultaneous embeddings of upward planar digraphs, which are relevant to topics such as VLSI design and network routing. The paper presents algorithms and complexity results for these problems, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves combinatorial and graph-theoretic arguments, which could place it in the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses implications of its results on network routing, which could relate to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
